182
00:12:50,210 --> 00:12:53,670
Your face really is an open book.

183
00:12:55,820 --> 00:12:58,190
So what happened?

184
00:12:59,770 --> 00:13:02,580
Well, it's not really a big deal,

185
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:07,140
but Mr. Okano saw me with Ida.

186
00:13:07,140 --> 00:13:10,470
I think he doesn't like me anymore.

187
00:13:10,470 --> 00:13:14,400
Then he called off his promise to treat me to ramen.

188
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:19,490
I was really looking forward to the treat. It's so unfortunate.

189
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,430
Aoki...

190
00:13:23,370 --> 00:13:25,790
That is a big deal.

191
00:13:29,140 --> 00:13:30,790
Is it?

192
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:34,430
I'm ticked off! What a jerk!

193
00:13:34,430 --> 00:13:37,270
Hashimoto, something appeared behind you.

194
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:40,130
I bet he always says stuff carelessly without thinking it through.

195
00:13:40,130 --> 00:13:44,360
I was the same way. My persuasiveness is on another level.

196
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:46,700
Is that something to brag about?

197
00:13:48,610 --> 00:13:51,600
I guess... you're right.

198
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:54,170
You should file a complaint to a school forum.

199
00:13:54,170 --> 00:13:56,690
Aoki should just quit his lesson.

200
00:13:56,690 --> 00:14:00,490
- Why? Aoki hasn't done anything wrong.
- It's really fine.

201
00:14:00,490 --> 00:14:02,080
Don't fight, guys.

202
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:03,480
Let's go, Aoki.

203
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:05,810
I'm simply worried about Aoki.

204
00:14:05,810 --> 00:14:07,390
- Here you go.
- Here you go.

205
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:08,670
Thanks. Good work, guys.

206
00:14:08,670 --> 00:14:10,510
Excuse us.

207
00:14:11,140 --> 00:14:13,100
Excuse us.

208
00:14:17,870 --> 00:14:21,110
Should I go talk to Mr. Okano instead?

209
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:24,370
What? Forget it. Don't you have your practice today?

210
00:14:24,370 --> 00:14:27,690
- I'll skip it.
- You don't have to do that!

211
00:14:28,620 --> 00:14:32,670
He said he wouldn't tell anyone. It's already settled.

212
00:14:32,670 --> 00:14:36,170
If you're depressed about it, it's not settled.

213
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:39,010
Ida...

214
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:41,900
What do you want to do?

215
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:48,130
I want...

216
00:14:50,100 --> 00:14:54,680
to treasure the person who treasures me.

217
00:14:57,100 --> 00:15:00,390
Hey, do you have time today after your club?

218
00:15:00,390 --> 00:15:01,600
What?

219
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:04,450
Why don't we eat ramen? Just the two of us.

220
00:15:04,450 --> 00:15:07,330
I would refuse Mr. Okano, even if he invites me to.

221
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:10,740
It's a promise.

222
00:15:10,740 --> 00:15:13,770
Okay. See you later. Good luck with your club!

223
00:15:13,770 --> 00:15:15,320
Thanks.

224
00:15:18,830 --> 00:15:21,490
Aoki's test score went up again.

225
00:15:21,490 --> 00:15:24,890
You're good at drawing out a student's potential.

226
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:27,740
No, not at all.

227
00:15:27,740 --> 00:15:31,400
It was you who taught us in spartan methods back then,

228
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:34,170
that's why my score went up.

229
00:15:34,170 --> 00:15:37,250
That was good old days.

230
00:15:37,250 --> 00:15:43,270
I've been at this job for many decades. I've met lots of different students.

231
00:15:43,270 --> 00:15:48,350
Each of them had their own unique personality.

232
00:15:48,350 --> 00:15:54,450
Sometimes I think being a teacher is about watching over their individuality.

233
00:15:54,450 --> 00:15:58,450
Mr. Taniguchi, do you know about those two?

234
00:15:58,450 --> 00:16:00,240
